<h3><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/index.html">SEP</a></h3>
<p>New:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/dai-zhen/">Dai Zhen</a> by Frank Y. C. Chong and Chris Fraser.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/george-eliot/">George Eliot</a> by Clare Carlisle.</li>
</ol>
<p>Revised:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/infinity/">Infinity</a> by Kenny Easwaran, Alan Hájek, Paolo Mancosu, and Graham Oppy.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/dependence-ontological/">Ontological Dependence</a> by Tuomas E. Tahko and E. Jonathan Lowe.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/song-ming-confucianism/">Song-Ming Confucianism</a> by Justin Tiwald.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/paradoxes-contemporary-logic/">Paradoxes and Contemporary Logic</a> by Andrea Cantini and Riccardo Bruni.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/natural-law-ethics/">The Natural Law Tradition in Ethics</a> by Mark Murphy.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/hermeneutics/">Hermeneutics</a> by Theodore George.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/lawphil-nature/">The Nature of Law</a> by Emad Atiq, Andrei Marmor, and Alexander Sarch.</li>
</ol>
